<p class="lead"> On this page you will find information about a particular type of entry, a Late Entry: a special type entry which you may encounter during a search. The GRO Indexes contain some records of events in a particular year or quarter-year that relate to events which occurred in a earlier year or quarter-year (not necessarily the preceeding quarter). They are known as <em>Late Entries</em>. In these cases, the indexes often contain an special entry inserted in the quarter in which the event should have been registered that link towards the Late Entry. You will find here, how FreeBMD provides assistance in finding these late entries when searching and how you might interprete them. </p>

